    "They are specifically designed to mimic questions that could be posed by users in real-world scenarios.",
    "Dr.Spider, also a Spider derivative, incorporates 17 distinct perturbations across questions, databases, and SQL queries to holistically evaluate the robustness of text-to-SQL models.",
    "Specifically, Dr.Spider comprises 3 test sets with database perturbation, 9 test sets reflecting question perturbation, and 5 test sets with SQL perturbation.Bank-Financials derives from a finance database containing 4 tables, with the largest table containing 65 columns (see Figure 2).",
